.TH "HPC\-COMPOSE\-DOCTOR\-READINESS" "1" "" "hpc\-compose 0.1.43" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
hpc\-compose\-doctor\-readiness \- Explain or run one service readiness probe from the current host
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
hpc\-compose doctor readiness [OPTIONS]
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
Explain or run one service readiness probe from the current host
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB-f\fR, \fB--file\fR \fIFILE\fR
Compose specification file to read; if omitted, use the active context compose file or fall back to compose.yaml.
.TP
\fB--format\fR \fIFORMAT\fR
Output format. Possible values: text, json.
.TP
\fB--service\fR \fISERVICE\fR
Service readiness probe to inspect; inferred when exactly one service defines readiness.
.TP
\fB--run\fR
Run the readiness probe from the current host instead of only explaining it.
.TP
\fB--log\-file\fR \fIPATH\fR
Log file to inspect for readiness.type=log when \-\-run is used.
.TP
\fB--timeout\-seconds\fR \fISECONDS\fR
Override the probe timeout for this doctor run only.
.TP
\fB--color\fR \fIWHEN\fR
Controls colored output. Default: auto. Possible values: auto, always, never.
.TP
\fB--quiet\fR
Suppress progress indicators and non\-essential labels.
.TP
\fB--profile\fR \fINAME\fR
Profile name to load from .hpc\-compose/settings.toml.
.TP
\fB--settings\-file\fR \fIPATH\fR
Explicit settings file path; defaults to upward search for .hpc\-compose/settings.toml.
.TP
\fB-h\fR, \fB--help\fR
Print help (see a summary with '\-h').
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
hpc\-compose doctor
hpc\-compose doctor cluster\-report
hpc\-compose doctor readiness \-f compose.yaml \-\-service api
hpc\-compose doctor readiness \-f compose.yaml \-\-service api \-\-run
hpc\-compose doctor mpi\-smoke \-f compose.yaml \-\-service trainer
hpc\-compose doctor fabric\-smoke \-f compose.yaml \-\-service trainer \-\-checks auto
.fi
